\begin_inset Formula $\beta dt$
\end_inset

 of buyers arrive at the platform.
 Each new buyer arrives with a single job that he proposes to one of the
 available sellers.
 The seller is chosen uniformly at random from the pool of available workers.
 If the buyer's job is accepted, the buyer stays until his job is completed;
 otherwise, he leaves the platform.
 Assume 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta\tau<1$
\end_inset

 which implies that collectively, it is physically possible for sellers
