 In a steady state, the mass of available sellers is 
\begin_inset Formula $1-\brho$
\end_inset

, and so,
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\beta_{A}:=\frac{\beta}{1-\bar{\rho}}.\label{eq:beta_A-definition}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Note that 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

 is the flow rate at which buyers arrive at the platform, while 
\begin_inset Formula $\betaa$
\end_inset

 is the Poisson rate at which buyers arrive to available sellers.
\begin_inset Foot
status open

