In more detail, on the one hand, an individual available seller faces a
 stochastic arrival process, such that the probability of arrival of a new
 buyer over time interval 
\begin_inset Formula $dt$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{A}dt+o(dt)$
\end_inset

.
 On the other hand, available sellers jointly face the deterministic arrival
 process of buyers, such that over time interval 
\begin_inset Formula $dt$
\end_inset

 the mass 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{A}dt$
\end_inset

 of buyers arrive.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 The particularly simple form of the relation between the two in Eq.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:beta_A-definition"

\end_inset

